    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Generally, constructing or composing a whole object or component by putting parts together; specifically refers to the construction of light forms of woodwork, including furniture constructed with dovetail or other joints, and features such as doors or staircases in buildings.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
